metadata.name: H-3 In The 808
metadata.description:
I took this photo from a "Magnum PI" helicopter above Interstate H-3 and the Ko ªolau Range on O'ahu, Hawai'i. The deep fog along the ridge forced us to take "the long way home" around the mountains. The opportunity to physically fly above O'ahu versus taking photos from a drone allows you to "feel" while shooting. I hope this image conveys those feelings of hovering over one of the most pieces of land in the world. 

This photo is the first of my 808 series documenting my time on the Hawaiian Islands...in the air, on the land, and in the sea.
